<dl id="n53122g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122g">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122g"> 122(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> speak to her of gold &amp; silver <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122g"><li>FW 28.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n53122g">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n53122g">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122g">MS BL 47476a-150</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:323 <a name="ad7" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad7.htm#n53122g">Draft: I.1&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Le roi no r&eacute;sista pas au d&eacute;sir de M&acirc;y&acirc;, et il dit &agrave; ses serviteurs : <p>&laquo;Courez dans les jardins, et <mark>parez-les d&apos;argent et d&apos;or</mark>. Attachez aux arbres des voiles pr&eacute;cieux. Que tout soit en f&ecirc;te pour le passage de la reine.&raquo; <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 15</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: After ten months Maya went into the gardens of the palace &mdash; now adorned for her in gold and silver, and as she stood under a sal tree she gave birth to a son. At this, trees of all seasons bore flowers and their fruits ripened. The child was named Siddharta and this was his royal name and his family name was Gautama. </mm> </dd></dl>
